# StudyForge Core

NX monorepo: `web` (React 19 + Vite, :4200), `admin` (Next.js 16, :4201), `functions`, `extension`, `shared-types`.

**Never use MUI.** Use shadcn/ui + Tailwind in `web` and `admin`.

## Commands (always via NX from workspace root)

```bash
NX_DAEMON=false NX_ISOLATE_PLUGINS=false yarn nx run web:typecheck
NX_DAEMON=false NX_ISOLATE_PLUGINS=false yarn nx run web:lint
NX_DAEMON=false NX_ISOLATE_PLUGINS=false yarn nx run admin:typecheck
NX_DAEMON=false NX_ISOLATE_PLUGINS=false yarn nx run admin:lint
NX_DAEMON=false NX_ISOLATE_PLUGINS=false yarn nx run functions:serve
```

## Domain Language

Read [CONTEXT.md](../../CONTEXT.md) for StudyForge terminology (directory, artifact, rule, generation status, etc.). Use those terms consistently; update the glossary via `/grill-with-docs`.

## Must Follow

- RTK Query for all API calls — never `httpsCallable` in components
- Providers orchestrate hooks only — no `useState`/`useSelector`/`useEffect` in providers
- Serializable Redux only — no Dates, Maps, Sets, class instances
- Check `@shared-types` and `web/src/types/` before creating new types
- No type assertions (`as any`, `@ts-ignore`) — use type guards and Zod

## Deploy

- **Web hosting**: never `firebase deploy --only hosting` — push to `main`; CI (`firebase-hosting-merge.yml`) deploys.
- **Functions**: `yarn nx run functions:deploy` when explicitly requested.

## Gotchas

1. Emulator `--project` must match `NX_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID` or callables fail with CORS 404
2. Deploy secret: `FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_STUDY_FORGE_202604` (project `study-forge-202604`)
3. Admin privileged reads via Firebase Admin SDK server-side only
4. Pre-existing lint warning in `RuleSelector.tsx` (accessible-emoji) — do not flag as new

